        <title locale="en_US">Revision of the Australo-Papuan genus &lt;i&gt;Spilopyra &lt;/i&gt;Baly (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Spilopyrinae)</title>
        <abstract locale="en_US">The genus &lt;i&gt;Spilopyra&lt;/i&gt; Baly is revised, with five valid species, three new: &lt;i&gt;S.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;safrina&lt;/i&gt; &lt;b&gt;sp.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;nov.,&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;S.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;scratchley&lt;/i&gt; &lt;b&gt;sp.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;nov.,&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;S.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;semiramis&lt;/i&gt; &lt;b&gt;sp.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;nov.,&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;S.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;stirlingi&lt;/i&gt; Lea, 1914, &lt;i&gt;S.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;sumptuosa&lt;/i&gt; Baly, 1860. &lt;i&gt;Spilopyra&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;stirlingi&lt;/i&gt; is a senior synonym of &lt;i&gt;S.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;flavicornis&lt;/i&gt; Weise, 1923 (syn. &lt;b&gt;nov.).&lt;/b&gt; Lectotypes are designated for &lt;i&gt;S.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;stirlingi&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;S.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;sumptuosa.&lt;/i&gt; The genus may be considerably more diverse, as three of the species are known from just 7 specimens. &lt;i&gt;Spilopyra&lt;/i&gt; species occur from northern New South Wales, Australia, to central New Guinea, and known hosts are Sapindaceae.</abstract>
